abstract: Survey results suggests their views and priorities are far more alike than different, despite labels like moderate or progressive, centrist or liberal.
snippet: Survey results suggests their views and priorities are far more alike than different, despite labels like moderate or progressive, centrist or liberal.
lead_paragraph: The four Democratic candidates at the top of the polls heading into the Iowa caucuses have been paired by pundits into what they like to call lanes. It’s a highway analogy, as in “stay in your lane.” One, seen as more progressive and liberal, contains Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren. The other, consisting of Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, is more centrist and moderate.

snippet: Amy Klobuchar’s campaign signaled no interest in such a plan, under which each candidate would encourage supporters to back the other in certain precincts.
lead_paragraph: Aides to former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. are discussing the possibility of seeking an alliance with Senator Amy Klobuchar in next week’s Iowa caucuses, a plan that would involve a pledge to help each other in precincts where one of them does not have enough support to win delegates.

abstract: Democrats who once derided him now want him to testify at President Trump’s impeachment trial while some of his erstwhile Republican friends are throwing him to the curb.
snippet: Democrats who once derided him now want him to testify at President Trump’s impeachment trial while some of his erstwhile Republican friends are throwing him to the curb.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Not long ago, they called him “too extreme,” “aggressively and dangerously wrong” and “downright dangerous.” They called him “nutty,” “reckless” and “far outside the mainstream.”

abstract: Readers react to Bret Stephens’s argument that the Democrats’ far-left candidates are as “reckless” as the president, leaving “none of the above” as a viable option.

abstract: As Mr. Biden campaigned in the state, residents appeared unmoved: “I don’t think much about anything Joni Ernst says.”
snippet: As Mr. Biden campaigned in the state, residents appeared unmoved: “I don’t think much about anything Joni Ernst says.”
lead_paragraph: MUSCATINE, Iowa — Senator Joni Ernst of Iowa, a Republican, wondered aloud about her Democratic constituents as they wrestled with a final decision before the looming Iowa caucuses, particularly those considering supporting former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.

byline_person: [{'firstname': 'Gail', 'middlename': None, 'lastname': 'Collins', 'qualifier': None, 'title': None, 'role': 'reported', 'organization': '', 'rank': 1}, {'firstname': 'Bret', 'middlename': None, 'lastname': 'Stephens', 'qualifier': None, 'title': None, 'role': 'reported', 'organization': '', 'rank': 2}]

abstract: With or without witnesses, Trump’s trial shows that the antifederalists were right to question the Senate’s purpose.
snippet: With or without witnesses, Trump’s trial shows that the antifederalists were right to question the Senate’s purpose.
lead_paragraph: Last week, after Senate Republicans voted unanimously to approve their leader Mitch McConnell’s rules for President Trump’s impeachment trial — fast-tracking the process and putting up barriers to the production of evidence and witnesses, Representative Jerry Nadler of New York, one of seven impeachment managers, despaired over the strong chance that voters would not get a fair, comprehensive hearing of the case against the president.

abstract: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
snippet: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden has no trouble lingering in place, wherever he is, especially if there’s a point he wants to finish — or start. Generally it does not matter how many people are prodding him along or waiting out in the cold. And it seemed important to Biden that I hear what he was talking about right now before we finished.
